y approximately $0.20 for the remainder of 2003. The non-recurring charges associated with the refinancing will be cash call premiums and refinancing expenses of approximately $25 million, un-amortized bond discount write-offs of approximately $10 million and deferred debt issuance cost write-offs of approximately $9 million, or approximately $0.72 per share in the first quarter of 2003. Commenting on the refinancing and redemption of its notes and debentures, Larry Castellani, the Company's Chairman and Chief Executive Officer said, "By calling our high interest bearing debt, we will significantly
