ROANOKE, Va., April 29, 2010  Advance Auto Parts, Inc., (NYSE: AAP), a leading automotive aftermarket retailer of parts, batteries, accessories, and maintenance items, announced today the closing of its Senior Unsecured Notes offering. The Company completed the offering of $300 million in principal amount of 5.75% Senior Unsecured Notes due 2020 at an issue price of 99.587%. The company will use the proceeds of the offering to pay off and retire the $200 million of outstanding indebtedness under its term loan, reduce $75 million of borrowings under its revolving credit facility, pay transaction fees and expenses and for general corporate purposes.
"We are very pleased by the strong investor interest in our notes. This transaction secures long-term financing that aligns with the Company's growth strategies while diversifying the Company's debt stakeholders," said Michael A. Norona, Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer. "We are also proud of our recent upgrade to investment grade status (BBB-) by Standard & Poor's, as we believe it is a positive affirmation of our operational performance, solid operating cash flows, and strong financial metrics."
Banc of America Securities LLC and J.P. Morgan Securities Inc. acted as joint book-running managers of the debt offering. The offering is being made solely by means of a prospectus supplement and accompanying prospectus, which has been filed with the SEC. A copy of the prospectus for the offering may be obtained on the SEC's website, . Alternatively, you may request it by contacting Banc of America Securities LLC, Attention: Prospectus Department, 100 West 33
