 means, for any period, Adjusted Consolidated Net Income for such period, plus, without duplication and to the extent deducted from revenues in determining Adjusted Consolidated Net Income, the sum of (a) consolidated interest expense for such period, (b) the aggregate amount of letter of credit fees accrued during such period, (c) the aggregate amount of income tax expense for such period, (d) all depreciation and amortization expense for such period and (e) other non-cash charges for such period (excluding any non-cash charges that constitute an accrual of or reserve for future cash payments), and minus, without duplication and to the extent added to revenues in determining Adjusted Consolidated Net Income for such period, all non-cash gains during such period, all as determined on a consolidated basis with respect to Holdings and the Subsidiaries in accordance with GAAP.
Consolidated EBITDA
 
 means, for any period, the sum of Consolidated EBITDA for such period plus Consolidated Rent Expense for such period.
